{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Sixth review BLOCK remediation: accepted f2d563e40c2d4a440/f7c91ba11e3ed1ba8/fa50bab555cf4d878. Re-sign recovery cannot call compute_validity because it has a REVIEW_RESULT sidecar rather than a certified attestation; the plan now persists the pre-LLM related_material snapshot in the sidecar and validates it through a shared pin-health helper while retaining the own-material guard. Accepted fbfc79c5e7f9444b3 by specifying a key-local ConfigError catch modeled on mcp_readonly(), with an exact structured warning and no claim that verify.* generally fails open. Also resolved retained drift-refresh/profile/interface advisories by defining exact delegated checks, intentional reopen behavior, same-current-policy/different-call-site profile semantics, additive health compatibility, and rollback. Rerunning before downstream review."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784543102814266001,"uuid":"616f0b34-0710-4b2e-a7f0-71d83333d4d8"}